 default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 28</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.4.5" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.5.52" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 52</bibl>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>his last --s to us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 127</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to do an o.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 3, 14</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.217" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 217</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.344" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 344</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.111" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 111</bibl>. <cit><quote>to make an o.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 15</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.200" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.8.59" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 8, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 61</bibl>. Peculiar use: <cit><quote>may one be pardoned and retain the o.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 3, 56</bibl></cit> (i.e. the fruits of his crime).
